task.summary:
Re-created the initial schema and set up flyway
I set up flyway so that if we build locally we don't have to worry about manually applying SQL scripts, in their correct order. I also refactored the initial schema to match our currently schema on the uploader, and to have less, useless information. Going to migrate the DAOs from the uploader.
Created jooq files off of new database schema

Made the AssignmentDAO work with the jooq classes.
After generating the jooq code, I had to majorly refactor the DAO classes. I already thought that the DAO classes were already refactored from Sprint 3, but apparently I was wrong. This subtask is going to take more time.
Removed page since we have no pages on the server.

Set up MariaDB database integration for the ERA server.
I have set up and tested MariaDB database integration with the ERA Server. I implemented the stubbed DAOs, changed the command line options to allow specifying a connection string, and added a new `#uploadCourses` API to test the database functionality.

Added CONTRIBUTING doc that describes how the server works. Fixed bugs
I added a CONTRIBUTING doc that will hopefully allow Cam to develop on the server better. I also fixed some of the bugs with the new API call I implemented last sprint.
